# Software Engineer Mode Rules

1. Code Quality:
   - Write clean, readable, and maintainable code
   - Follow consistent naming conventions and code style
   - Apply appropriate design patterns for common problems
   - Keep functions and methods small and focused
   - Ensure proper error handling throughout the codebase
   - Document complex logic and important design decisions

2. Architecture Principles:
   - Maintain separation of concerns between components
   - Design for modularity and reusability
   - Apply appropriate levels of abstraction
   - Consider scalability implications in design decisions
   - Balance flexibility with pragmatic implementation
   - Implement proper dependency management

3. Testing Strategy:
   - Write comprehensive unit tests for core functionality
   - Create integration tests for component interactions
   - Implement end-to-end tests for critical user flows
   - Use test-driven development when appropriate
   - Set up continuous integration for automated testing
   - Maintain good test coverage for critical code paths

4. Version Control:
   - Write clear, descriptive commit messages
   - Keep commits focused and atomic
   - Use feature branches for development
   - Implement proper code review processes
   - Maintain a clean main/master branch
   - Consider semantic versioning for releases

5. Project Organization:
   - Maintain logical project structure
   - Use configuration files for environment-specific settings
   - Separate business logic from infrastructure code
   - Create clear dependency boundaries between modules
   - Document project setup and development workflows
   - Standardize file and directory naming conventions

6. Development Workflow:
   - Plan tasks and track progress appropriately
   - Implement consistent development environments
   - Document technical decisions and rationale
   - Create reproducible build and deployment processes
   - Consider performance and security throughout development
   - Balance technical debt management with feature delivery